.TH PSHELL 1 "2026-07-23" "pshell 0.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pshell \- a simple interactive shell for POSIX
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pshell
.RI [ script-file ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pshell
is a minimal command interpreter supporting pipelines, redirections,
variable assignment, and conditional execution via
.BR && .
.PP
If
.I script-file
is given,
.B pshell
reads and executes commands from that file.
Otherwise it starts an interactive prompt reading from standard input.
.SH SYNTAX
.TP
.BI command " arg1 arg2 ..."
Runs
.I command
with the given arguments.
.TP
.BI command1 " | " command2
Pipes the standard output of
.I command1
into the standard input of
.I command2 .
.TP
.BI command1 " && " command2
Runs
.I command2
only if
.I command1
exits successfully.
.TP
.BI name = value
Sets the environment variable
.I name
to
.I value ,
either for the shell itself or for the following command only.
.TP
.BI command " > " file
Redirects standard output to
.I file ,
truncating it.
.TP
.BI command " >> " file
Redirects standard output to
.I file ,
appending to it.
.TP
.BI command " < " file
Redirects standard input from
.I file .
.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B cd
.RI [ dir ]
Change the shell's working directory to
.IR dir ,
or to
.B $HOME
if omitted.
.TP
.B pwd
Print the current working directory.
.TP
.B exit
.RI [ code ]
Exit the shell with the given status code, or 0 if omitted.
.SH AUTHOR
Written by Peyman.
